headline.main: OUR CRAFT WARNED; Navy Says Ships Were Called From Voyages for 'Instructions' CAPITAL IS NOT UNEASY Washington Doubts That New Tokyo Premier Will Seek a Break With U.S. SHIPS IN PACIFIC GO TO SAFE PORTS

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 17 -- American merchant ships in Asiatic waters have been ordered by the Navy Department to put into friendly ports because of the Japanese crisis.
abstract: 14 ships carrying war materials to Vladivostok believed affected by Navy Dept order to Pacific merchant shipping
